# SortableList

`TxSortableList` renders an ordered list and emits a reordered array when the user drags one item onto another. Use it for small to medium user-managed lists where native HTML5 Drag & Drop is acceptable.

Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/sortable-list/src/types.ts`, `TxSortableList.vue`, and `sortable-list.test.ts`.

## Basic Usage

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="SortableListSortableListDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const list = ref([
    { id: 'one', title: 'One' },
    { id: 'two', title: 'Two' },
    { id: 'three', title: 'Three' },
  ])
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxSortableList v-model="list">
      <template #item="{ item, dragging }">
        <div :class="['sortable-row', { 'sortable-row--dragging': dragging }]">
          {{ item.title }}
        </div>
      </template>
    </TxSortableList>
  </template>
---
:::

## Composition Examples

### Drag Handle Mode

When `handle=true`, drag must start from an element inside `[data-tx-sort-handle="true"]`.

```vue
<template>
  <TxSortableList v-model="steps" handle @reorder="saveOrder">
    <template #item="{ item }">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 p-3">
        <button type="button" data-tx-sort-handle="true" aria-label="Drag item">☰</button>
        <span>{{ item.title }}</span>
      </div>
    </template>
  </TxSortableList>
</template>
```

### Persisting Reorder

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
const tasks = ref([{ id: 'draft' }, { id: 'review' }, { id: 'ship' }])

async function persistOrder({ items }: { items: Array<{ id: string }> }) {
  tasks.value = items
  await api.saveTaskOrder(items.map(item => item.id))
}
</script>

<template>
  <TxSortableList v-model="tasks" @reorder="persistOrder" />
</template>
```

## Interaction Contract

- The root renders `role="list"`; each item renders `role="listitem"`.
- Each item must have a stable string `id`; `id` is used for Vue keys and drag bookkeeping.
- Items are draggable unless `disabled=true`. Disabled mode also blocks drag start, drag over, drop reordering, and emitted reorder events.
- `handle=false` allows drag start from anywhere inside the item.
- `handle=true` requires the drag event target or one of its ancestors to match `[data-tx-sort-handle="true"]`.
- Drag start stores the item id in `dataTransfer`, uses an empty drag image, and marks the item as dragging.
- Drag over marks the hovered item and calls `preventDefault()` only during an active drag.
- Drop clears drag state, ignores missing ids and same-index drops, then emits `update:modelValue` and `reorder` with the reordered copy.
- `dragend` always clears drag and hover state.
- Reordering uses shallow array copies; item objects are preserved.

## API

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `modelValue` | `SortableListItem[]` | required | Ordered list data. Every item must provide a stable string `id`. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables drag interactions and reorder emits. |
| `handle` | `boolean` | `false` | Requires drag start from `[data-tx-sort-handle="true"]`. |

### SortableListItem

| Field | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `id` | `string` | Stable identity used for keys and drag state. Additional fields are preserved. |

### Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `update:modelValue` | `SortableListItem[]` | Emitted with the reordered array after a valid drop. |
| `reorder` | `{ from: number, to: number, items: SortableListItem[] }` | Emitted after a valid reorder with source index, target index, and reordered items. |

### Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `item` | `{ item, dragging }` | Custom renderer for each item. Falls back to the item `id`. |

## Best Practices

- Use stable persisted ids; never use array indexes as ids for reorderable data.
- Update the bound array from `v-model` and persist from `reorder` when server order matters.
- Use `handle` for rows that contain buttons, links, inputs, or selectable text.
- Keep list sizes modest. For very long lists, combine a different drag strategy with virtualization instead of rendering every row draggable.
- Provide visible drag affordances in the item slot; the component does not inject a handle UI.
- Do not use this component for keyboard-only sortable flows without adding a separate accessible reorder control.

## Review Notes

- **Accessibility note:** The component exposes list/listitem semantics but native drag-and-drop is pointer-centric. Provide a separate keyboard-accessible reorder flow for settings screens, command palettes, or enterprise forms where keyboard-only use is required.
- **Data note:** Reorder emits a shallow copied array and preserves item object references. Persist by stable `id`, not by index or object identity.
- **Verified coverage:** `sortable-list.test.ts` checks list semantics, slot props, fallback item ids, reorder emits, same-item drop suppression, disabled blocking, handle-only drag start, and dragend state cleanup.

